  "text": "For our computations we take the mathematically derived unsplit PML of [CITATION_1] . In the experiments of [CITATION_2] , this layer has clearly shown to be prone to the undesirable growth of the solution for long integration times. We note that originally the PML of [CITATION_3] was constructed for the two-dimensional Cartesian TE Maxwell equations. As, however, the axial coordinate of the cylindrical system is essentially Cartesian, the layer of [CITATION_4] can be exported to the setup shown in Fig. 2 with no change at all:",
